# Weekly Debrief (Monday)

When Deekshant sends `Monday — weekly debrief — DD MMM,YY` (or `Monday — weekly plan + metrics` with the same data), respond with **all 8 sections** — no shortcuts.

This is **not** the `resolve-custom-food-macros` skill. That skill only patches `food_logs` for custom items with missing macros. Weekly debrief is the integrated training + nutrition + recovery judgment for the week.

## Before debriefing

1. Read Monday paste metrics and prior-week rollups (app fills longest run, avg sleep, knee, cigs from `week-stats.js` contract in `WEEK-STATS-SPEC.md`)
2. Pull prior week's daily logs: runs, workouts, food, vitals — from app debrief paste or Supabase
3. Compare **planned vs actual** mileage, sessions completed, protein/kcal patterns
4. Read `personal-details.md` for race timeline, injury history, blood markers (triglycerides 227)
5. **Weight:** ±0.5 kg = noise; **2+ week trends = signal** — never react to a single Monday weigh-in alone
6. Check body comp scan if included — do not merge scan into Monday vitals (see `body-comp.mdc`)

## Section 1 — WEEK SCORE

Score /10: Training · Nutrition · Recovery · Adherence → composite + one-line verdict for the **week**, not today only.

## Section 2 — METRICS & TRENDS

| Metric | Prior week | Trend / signal |
|--------|------------|----------------|
| Weight | Monday AM kg | vs prior Mondays — noise or signal |
| Waist | in | direction over 2+ weeks if data exists |
| Mileage | actual / planned km | 10% rule context for next week |
| Long run | km + date | progression toward 18–20 km |
| Avg sleep | h | floor 7h — impact on load |
| Knee | worst status | cadence / volume link |
| Cigs/day | avg | flag only if relevant to recovery or deviation |

State what changed and **why it matters** for the next block.

## Section 3 — TRAINING REVIEW

- Sessions: planned vs completed (runs, bodyweight, rest honored or not)
- Long run: distance, pace, RPE, knee, cadence vs targets
- Strength: volume, RPE, knee-friendly compliance (no squats/lunges on leg-freshness days until gym phase)
- Load decision inputs: apply **10% weekly mileage rule** explicitly when setting next week's km

## Section 4 — NUTRITION REVIEW

Coach-owned — **not tracked as C/F/P macros in the app**.

- Protein floor 140–150 g: estimate adherence from food logs (% of days on floor)
- Calorie bracket: deficit appropriate for ≤0.5 kg/week fat loss? too aggressive?
- Carb timing: pre-run fuel, post-run recovery, rest-day reduction — qualitative vs plan
- Triglycerides / refined carbs: flag sweets, juice, fried food, alcohol if logged or inferred
- Show protein/calorie math briefly when citing specific days

Do **not** output a macro dashboard. Judge structure and adherence, not gram-level carb/fat targets.

## Section 5 — DEVIATIONS & ROOT CAUSES

Week-level patterns only (day-level detail belongs in daily debriefs).

Each item: planned vs actual · severity (Minor/Moderate/Critical) · mechanistic why it matters across the week.

## Section 6 — LOAD & RECOVERY DECISION

Explicit decisions for Week N+1:

- Next week total km and long-run distance (with 10% cap math)
- Run / bodyweight / rest layout
- Sleep or stress constraints
- Knee modifiers (reduce, hold, or progress)
- Nutrition adjustments (protein anchor, calorie bracket, carb timing notes) — prose only

## Section 7 — WEEK N+1 PLAN

Structured table **Mon–Sun with dates on every row**. Each day includes:

- Training type (Run / Bodyweight / Rest / Active Recovery)
- Run: type, distance, pace, cadence cue, key instruction — or NA
- Strength: exercises, sets, RPE — or NA
- Meals: what to eat with portions
- Protein target (g), calorie bracket, carb timing, recovery note, one-line directive

After issuing the plan:

1. Add to `WEEK_PLANS` in `coach/week-plans.py`
2. Run `python3 seed-plans.py` (paste SQL if RLS blocks REST)
3. **Archive the report:** user invokes `save-weekly-debrief` skill → `coach_debriefs` in Supabase → Week tab read-only display

## Section 8 — COACH'S NOTE

One firm paragraph. No bullets. No hedging. Race timeline awareness (6 Sep 2026).

